Package: ecoregionr
Title: Environmental Bioregionalization and Clustering Toolkit for Africa
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R:
    person("Mohamed Jumanne", "Omari",
           email = "momari@ihi.or.tz",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-HERE"))
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for data-driven environmental
    bioregionalization of administrative units using multi-source raster
    covariates (climate, elevation, land cover, population, species
    richness, etc.).  The package implements two complementary clustering
    strategies: (1) Unconstrained PCA + consensus k-means — maximises
    within-cluster environmental homogeneity without spatial constraints;
    and (2) Spatially constrained SKATER clustering — guarantees that
    every bioregion forms a geographically contiguous zone, making the
    resulting regions operationally deployable as administrative units.
    Supporting utilities cover raster extraction, categorical composition
    summarisation, median imputation, interactive Leaflet maps, static
    publication-quality ggplot maps, cluster heatmaps, and auto-generated
    natural-language bioregion descriptions.  The package was developed
    for the Vector Grid Africa programme but is fully generic and can be
    applied to any country or region.
